    "what_description": "Salix alba is a deciduous tree species that belongs to the family Salicaceae. It is native to Europe, Western Asia, and North Africa, and has been naturalized in other parts of the world. The tree typically grows to a height of 10-15 meters, with a broad, rounded crown and a straight, columnar trunk. The bark is grayish-white, with horizontal lenticels, and the leaves are ovate-lanceolate, 6-12 cm long, with a serrated margin and a rounded base. The leaves are arranged oppositely on the twig, and are dark green on the upper surface and pale green on the lower surface.",
