    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Salix alba are inflammation, which can be alleviated by its anti-inflammatory properties, and skin irritation, caused by its astringent and antiseptic properties. Diarrhea, a symptom of gastroenteritis, can be treated with Salix alba due to its ability to reduce inflammation and soothe the digestive tract. Additionally, it is also used to promote wound healing, reduce eczema symptoms, and alleviate rheumatism, while also providing relief from insect bites and fever. Salix alba has antiseptic and antifungal properties, making it effective in treating skin infections, wounds, and fungal infections, as well as digestive issues such as gout and psoriasis. Furthermore, it is used to treat boils, mouth ulcers, varicose veins, burns, bruises, and boils, and has been shown to reduce the severity of digestive issues.",
