    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Salix alba are anti-inflammatory, which are attributed to the presence of salicin, a bioactive compound that belongs to the flavonoid class. The antioxidant properties of Salix alba are responsible for its ability to scavenge free radicals and reduce oxidative stress, a mechanism that is mediated by bioactive compounds such as phenolic acids and saponins. The antimicrobial properties of Salix alba are utilized to treat various infections, a function that is attributed to the presence of volatile oils and other bioactive compounds. Additionally, Salix alba exhibits diuretic properties, which are beneficial in treating conditions such as hypertension and edema, a function that is mediated by the bioactive compounds salicin and salicylic acid. Furthermore, the analgesic properties of Salix alba are utilized to treat pain, a function that is attributed to the presence of bioactive compounds such as salicin and salicylic acid.",
