    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Salix alba are salicin, salicylic acid, quercetin, flavonoids, and tannins. Salicin, a glycoside, is hydrolyzed to salicylic acid in the body, which has anti-inflammatory and analgesic properties, acting as an inhibitor of COX-1 and COX-2 enzymes. Quercetin, a flavonoid, exhibits anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities by scavenging free radicals and inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines. Flavonoids, including quercetin, also possess antimicrobial properties, while tannins contribute to the plant's astringent and antiseptic effects, protecting against infections and promoting wound healing. The combination of these constituents in Salix alba provides a synergistic effect, making it a valuable plant in traditional medicine for treating various inflammatory and painful conditions.",
