    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Salix alba improperly include inducing allergic reactions due to its sap's allergenic properties, causing nausea and gastrointestinal distress as a result of its high tannin content, exacerbating asthma symptoms in individuals sensitive to salicylates, and increasing the risk of bleeding due to its antiplatelet and anticoagulant properties, which can lead to hemorrhaging and bruising. These side effects occur because Salix alba's compounds interact with the body's biological systems in complex ways, affecting various physiological processes and potentially leading to adverse reactions. The improper use of Salix alba, such as consuming excessive amounts or applying its sap topically without proper precautions, can worsen these side effects. Furthermore, individuals with pre-existing medical conditions, such as asthma or bleeding disorders, are particularly vulnerable to the adverse effects of Salix alba. The risk of side effects is also increased in individuals taking medications that interact with Salix alba's compounds."
